	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=43848><span id= >gdcurry</span></a><br><span id=notbold>20 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I'm curious as to two things:<br>1) Does the ghoulbane still drop fron the Shin Lord?<br>and<br>2) What are the economics of questing versus camping a rare spawn?<br><br>I cannot answer the first, but as to the second, I have my opinions.&nbsp;&nbsp;One rare spawn dropping perhaps 2-3 ghoulbanes per day, versus many different spawns each of which drops the necessary item on average 30-40 times per day.  I know I've destroyed several opportunities at another ghoulbane being created by destroying the blade on the gobs in BB, and several I didn't destroy have sat unused and the corpse deteriorated before anyone picked it up.  Yet, it seems every time someone comes through looking for it they get it within 2-3 hours, no matter how many people there are looking for it.  Even if they are too low level to kill the mobs.  The new gobs in BB are great XP and cash for a group of 25-35, and one of the safest camps I've seen at that level.  I stayed there four days and went from level 29 to level 32, making about 1k plat in the process, and giving away blades left and right.<br><br>Then someone had the audacity to comment that the price on ghoulbane would go up because it was a quest instead of a drop.<br><br>I couldn't understand his reasoning, can anyone else shed some light on this?  I assumed that more ghoulbanes meant lower prices because of a higher supply and a lower demand.</p>&nbsp;<br>Ajia (Xev Server)<br>&lt;Povar-Tarew Artisans&gt;</td></td></tr>
